      "point": "Availability in Python",
      "description": "Python 3.12 introduces native support for NIS, providing an efficient and standardized way to access NIS maps within Python applications."
    },
    {
      "point": "Primary Components",
      "description": "The main components of the NIS module include `getpwnam()`, `getpwuid()`, `getnetbyname()`, `getnetbyaddr()`, and others. These functions allow for querying NIS maps related to users, groups, hosts, services, etc."
    },
    {
      "point": "Usage Example",
      "description": "Here's a simple example of using the NIS module to retrieve user information: \n```python\nimport getpass\nfrom pwd import getpwnam\nprint(getpwnam(getpass.getuser())['pw_gecos'])\n```"
    },
    {
      "point": "Version Notes",
      "description": "The NIS module is exclusive to Python 3.12 and later versions."
    },
    {
